#Write your code here.
################################################################################
## Reading the Data
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
# Visualizing the first 10 images from the training dataset
print("#######################################################################")
print("First 5 images from the training dataset")
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
for i in range(5):
    plt.subplot(1, 5, i+1)
    plt.imshow(x_train[i], cmap='Greys')
    plt.title(f"Label: {y_train[i]}")
    plt.axis('off')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
# Visualizing the count of different digits in y_train
print(" ")
print("#######################################################################")
print("Count of different digits in y_train")
counts = [0]*10  # initialize a list of 10 zeros, one for each digit
for label in y_train:
    counts[label] += 1
digits = [i for i in range(10)]  # [0, 1, 2, ..., 9]
plt.bar(digits, counts, color='black')
plt.xlabel('Digits')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.title('Count of different digits in y_train')
plt.xticks(digits)
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.show()
################################################################################
## Normalizing the Train and Test Data
# Flatten the images
x_train = x_train.reshape((x_train.shape[0], 28 * 28))
x_test = x_test.reshape((x_test.shape[0], 28 * 28))
# Normalize the data to [0, 1] range
x_train = x_train.astype('float32') / 255.0
x_test = x_test.astype('float32') / 255.0
################################################################################
## Convert to "One-Hot" Vectors Using the to_categorical Function
num_classes = 10
y_train = to_categorical (y_train, num_classes)
y_test_cat=to_categorical (y_test,num_classes)
################################################################################
## Defining the ANN Sequential Models
image_size=28*28
## 1. Standard Neural Network
model_standard = Sequential([
    Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(image_size,)),
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

## 2. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.2 for each layer)
model_dropout_M1 = Sequential([
    Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(image_size,)),
    Dropout(0.2),
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.2),
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.2),
    Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

## 3. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5 for each layer)
model_dropout_M2 = Sequential([
    Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(image_size,)),
    Dropout(0.5),
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.5),
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.5),
    Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

## 4. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5 for each layer)
model_dropout_M3 = Sequential([
    Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(image_size,)),
    Dropout(0.5),
    BatchNormalization(), ## Added to enhance result from 2k errors to 1k errors
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.5),
    BatchNormalization(), ## Added to enhance result from 2k errors to 1k errors
    Dense(8, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.5),
    BatchNormalization(), ## Added to enhance result from 2k errors to 1k errors
    Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])
################################################################################
## Compile model
model_standard.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', \
              metrics=['accuracy']) # Loss function = Categorical cross entropy
model_dropout_M1.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', \
              metrics=['accuracy']) # Loss function = Categorical cross entropy
model_dropout_M2.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', \
              metrics=['accuracy']) # Loss function = Categorical cross entropy
model_dropout_M3.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', \
              metrics=['accuracy']) # Loss function = Categorical cross entropy
################################################################################
## Summary of Base Model
print(" ")
print("#######################################################################")
print("Summary of the Base Models")
print(" ")
print("1.Standard Neural Network Model")
## 1. Standard Neural Network
model_standard.summary()
print(" ")
print("2. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.2 for each layer) Model")
## 2. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.2 for each layer)
model_dropout_M1.summary()
print(" ")
print("3. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5 for each layer) Model")
## 3. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5 for each layer)
model_dropout_M2.summary()
print(" ")
print("4. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5) & BatchNormalization Model")
## 3. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5 for each layer)
model_dropout_M3.summary()
################################################################################
## Fit the Model
print(" ")
print("#######################################################################")
print("Training the ANN Models")
print(" ")
print("1.Standard Neural Network Model")
checkpoint0 = ModelCheckpoint ("model weights.h0", monitor='val accuracy',
                                save_weights_only=True,mode= 'max',verbose=1)
reduce_lr0 = ReduceLROnPlateau (monitor= 'val_loss', factor=0.1,patience=4,
                                  min_lr=0.00001, model='auto')
callbacks0 = (checkpoint0, reduce_lr0)
history0=model_standard.fit(x_train,y_train,validation_split=0.1,epochs=50, \
                  batch_size=256,verbose=1,callbacks=callbacks0)
print(" ")
print("2. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.2 for each layer) Model")
checkpoint1 = ModelCheckpoint ("model weights.h1", monitor='val accuracy',
                                save_weights_only=True,mode= 'max',verbose=1)
reduce_lr1 = ReduceLROnPlateau (monitor= 'val_loss', factor=0.1,patience=4,
                                  min_lr=0.00001, model='auto')
callbacks1 = (checkpoint1, reduce_lr1)
history1=model_dropout_M1.fit(x_train,y_train,validation_split=0.1,epochs=50, \
                  batch_size=256,verbose=1,callbacks=callbacks1)
print(" ")
print("3. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5 for each layer) Model")
checkpoint2 = ModelCheckpoint ("model weights.h2", monitor='val accuracy',
                                save_weights_only=True,mode= 'max',verbose=1)
reduce_lr2 = ReduceLROnPlateau (monitor= 'val_loss', factor=0.1,patience=4,
                                  min_lr=0.00001, model='auto')
callbacks2 = (checkpoint2, reduce_lr2)
history2=model_dropout_M2.fit(x_train,y_train,validation_split=0.1,epochs=50, \
                  batch_size=256,verbose=1,callbacks=callbacks2)
print(" ")
print("4. Neural Network with Dropout (factor 0.5) & BatchNormalization Model")
checkpoint3 = ModelCheckpoint ("model weights.h3", monitor='val accuracy',
                                save_weights_only=True,mode= 'max',verbose=1)

                                  min_lr=0.00001, model='auto')

# Define function to print metrics
def print_metrics(model, x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test):
    y_train_pred = np.argmax(model.predict(x_train), axis=1)
    y_test_pred = np.argmax(model.predict(x_test), axis=1)

    print("Training Data Metrics:")
    print(classification_report(np.argmax(y_train, axis=1), y_train_pred))
    print('-'*50)
    print("\nTest Data Metrics:")
    print(classification_report(np.argmax(y_test_cat, axis=1), y_test_pred))
    print('-'*50)
    return y_test_pred
